<p>I need to trigger a function specifically after an user scroll almost at the bottom of the page then up until certain point. How do I do it properly?</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/Hv6xP.jpg" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/Hv6xP.jpg" alt="Image as helper"></a></p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-js lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>advertisement.refreshAd = function() {    $(window).scroll(function(event) {       if('almost at the end then scroll up to certain point')       {console.log('trigger refresh!');}    }); }</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>